Peter Dale Scott. Peter Dale Scott, author of "the Dallas Conspiracy," and "Crime and Coverups: Dallas-Watergate," discusses the connections between organized crime, drug trafficking, and the political elite. He points to the frequency of Cuban exile names in association with the JFK assassination, Watergate, and assorted CIA programs.
